# Rule: packages/<name>/src/README.md

Some packages do not have a `src/index.ts` barrel — the VS Code
extension's entry is `src/extension.ts`, for example. In those
cases the package MAY add a `src/README.md` next to the entry to
describe what the entry does.

The file must:

- one-line the purpose of the entry;
- list the entry file and what it exports;
- stay under 40 lines.

If a package has both `src/index.ts` and `src/<other>.ts`, prefer
the top-level `packages/<name>/README.md` (governed by
`.agents/rules/package-readme.md.rule`); do not also write a
`src/README.md` unless the entry's role is genuinely different
from the barrel's role.